{"word":"ἀγήραος","slug":"ἀγήραος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγήραος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>γήρας</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>not waxing old, undecaying</i>,<p/></div><div class='li750'><b>1. </b>of persons, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>; so, <el>ἀγήρως χρόνῳ</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, attic<p/></div>"}]}